        <div class="header">
            <div class="header-container">
                <h1><em>"Fall" in Love with Rocky Mountain National Park</em></h1>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="summary">
            <p>If you've never been to Colorado's beautiful Rocky Mountain National Park in the fall, you simply must go.  The park spans the Continental Divide and encompasses protected mountains, forests and alpine tundra.  It is known for Trail Ridge Road and Old Fall River Road, drives that pass aspen trees and rivers.  The park is situated between the towns of Estes Park to the east and Grand Lake to the West.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="wildlife">
            <h3><em>Wildlife</em></h3>
            <p>Rocky Mountain National Park is home to many species of animals including elk, mule deer, bighorn sheep, and moose.  It is not uncommon to see flocks of wild turkeys roaming in the grasses, or spy a huge heard of elk marching up the streets of Estes Park.  The unique sound of bull elk bugling is truly something amazing to witness.  Nearly 300 species of bird call this place home.</p>
